   <concept id="FAR_16_102" class="- topic/topic concept/concept " xtrc="">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">16.102</ph> Policies.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d954e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d982e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
						            Contracts resulting from sealed bidding shall be firm-fixed-price contracts or fixed-price contracts with economic price adjustment.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d982e15">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> Contracts negotiated under <xref href="Part_15.dita#FAR_Part_15"
                        base="i1109360"
                        outputclass="fm:Part"
                        class="- topic/xref ">part  15</xref> may be of any type or combination of types that will promote the Government’s interest, except as restricted in this part (see 
                     <xref href="https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title10-section3321&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external">10 U.S.C. 3321(a)</xref>
                     
                   and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title41-section3901&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                        scope="external"
                        format="html">41 U.S.C. 3901</xref>). Contract types not described in this regulation shall not be used, except as a deviation under <xref href="Subpart_1.4.dita#FAR_Subpart_1_4"
                        base="i1126600"
                        outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                        class="- topic/xref ">subpart  1.4</xref>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d982e32">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph> The cost-plus-a-percentage-of-cost system of contracting shall not be used (see 
                     <xref href="https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title10-section3322&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external">10 U.S.C. 3322(a)</xref>
                     
                   and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title41-section3905(a)&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                        scope="external"
                        format="html">41 U.S.C. 3905(a)</xref>). Prime contracts (including letter contracts) other than firm-fixed-price contracts shall, by an appropriate clause, prohibit cost-plus-a-percentage-of-cost subcontracts (see clauses prescribed in <xref href="Subpart_44.2.dita#FAR_Subpart_44_2"
                        base="i1073536"
                        outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                        class="- topic/xref ">subpart  44.2</xref> for cost-reimbursement contracts and <xref href="Subpart_16.2.dita#FAR_Subpart_16_2"
                        base="i1104838"
                        outputclass="fm:Subparts"
                        class="- topic/xref ">subparts  16.2</xref> and <xref href="Subpart_16.4.dita#FAR_Subpart_16_4"
                        base="i1104343"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">16.4</xref> for fixed-price contracts).</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d982e52">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph>
                  
						            No contract may be awarded before the execution of any determination and findings (D&amp;F’s) required by this part. Minimum requirements for the content of D&amp;F’s required by this part are specified in <xref href="1.704.dita#FAR_1_704"
                        base="i1126360"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">1.704</xref>.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
